readFromFile

public void readFromFile(java.io.File configurationFile)
Load configuration information from a file. If the filename ends with ".xml", the file is interpreted as a Java XML configuration file. Otherwise it is interpreted as a text config file (eg "key = value" on each line). Note that text files can only use Latin 1 (en-us) characters, while XML files can be UTF-8.
